HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 693
By Keisling
A RESOLUTION to recognize Billy Robbins on the occasion of his
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should specially recognize those citizens who have
performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their years of industry; and
WHEREAS, Billy Robbins is one such estimable person, who has served since 2012 as
executive director of the Byrdstown/Pickett County Chamber of Commerce, from which position
he will soon take his well-deserved retirement; and
WHEREAS, a 1968 graduate of Pickett County High School, Billy Robbins holds a
Bachelor of Science degree in Industrial Engineering with a minor in Business from Tennessee
Technological University and has completed a one-year Master of Business Administration
program; and
WHEREAS, a proud military veteran, Mr. Robbins served with distinction in the United
States Army from September 1972 to September 1974, working in Fire Direction Control; and
WHEREAS, during his military career, he saw duty in the United States, Germany and
Vietnam; he was trained to give data for 8MM cannon fire in an air mobile unit and also served
as Headquarters Battery Clerk for six months, reaching the rank of E-5 before receiving his
honorable discharge; and
WHEREAS, in 1975, Mr. Robbins became a partner and owner of Robbins Auto Service
in Byrdstown, which performed repairs and services on all makes of automobiles; he operated
the business until September 2002 and served generations of customers during those twenty-
seven years; and
WHEREAS, offering himself for public service, Billy Robbins was elected Mayor of the
City of Byrdstown in August 2002 and held that esteemed position until August 2010, rendering
